						               													<description>Lord Waldemar is celebrating his 80th birthday in his stately home and has invited numerous prominent guests. Baroness of Walloon-Brabant is expected with her entourage, as well as Sir Adam Stoneworth and Count Bobby of Wexford. Even the famous opera singer Barbette Brunette and former boxing champion Arnold Wendestein have announced their attendance. We are looking forward to this special occasion, which will of course take place at 5 p.m. sharp - at tea time.&amp;#10;&amp;#10;Unfortunately, there has also been an increase in burglaries and thefts in this noble area lately. For this reason, Lord Waldemar has hired a renowned detective who, of course, appears with his assistant. During the celebrations they should keep an eye on the property and the luxurious belongings of his guests. If that succeeds, Lord Waldemar will acknowledge it very much.&amp;#10;&amp;#10;Gameplay:&amp;#10;Roll the dice up to 3 times. Choose dice with the same number and flip (or remove) a tile from your board that matches the result of the dice.&amp;#10;Try to find valuable rooms or thieves and arrange your detectives correctly, so you can score them.&amp;#10;&amp;#10;End: If a player places his 5th detective-tile correctly, everyone count all their points. The player with the most points wins.&amp;#10;&amp;#10;</description>
